    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Been thinking about this and I disagree that the geth log should output you the error message. The interface should take care of in or output (good or bad). You create a transaction through the RPC and the RPC returns you an error. Callers take care of error handling so you should deal with the error\n\n![l5qkp3bcssnawtnnw-0wzej5uud1qgygu4x90ll-qbe](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/6264126/7053102/1e87e694-de33-11e4-8e12-6da11f11c667.png)\n\nIf a transaction is being created from the `geth console` it will display an error message there.\n",
